To Hindus, Veda is absolute and supreme kno=
wledge. Veda is considered to be the knowledge of the Imperishable Self. Un=
fortunately, absurdly superficial, utterly nonsensical and absolutely usele=
ss translations such as the above reduce Veda to the level of idle and flow=
ery poetry about external rites and rituals. Any student who is genuinely i=
