    *        *
 
Now, let me give my independent translation, inspired by A=
urobindo's work.
 
Sarasvati literally means "the one who faicilitates the =
flow". In Aurobindo's opinion, various deities and external symbols were us=
ed to symbolize various internal principles, *consistently* throughout RigV=
eda by various rishis. According to him, Saraswati symbolizes inspiration f=
rom Truth.
 
In yogic traditions, Ganga and Yamuna rivers symbolize the Ida=
 (Chandra) and Pingala (Surya) nadis and the hidden Sarasvati river symboli=
zes the hidden Sushumna nadi. When Kundalini shakti (power of self-awarenes=
s) flows in Sushumna nadi, one starts to transcend falsified notions of sel=
f (e.g. I am the body) and starts to realize one's true nature. Thus Sushum=
na nadi or Saraswati is the facilitator of the flow of Truth, i.e. awarenes=
s of True Self.
 
My independent translation:
 
1.3.10: The subtle energy c=
hannel that facilitates the flow of an awareness of True Self (sarasvatI), =
by being the controller of the racing horses (vAjinIvatI) of false notions =
of who we are and what Truth is (vAjebhiH) and thus purifies (pAvakAH) us (=
naH). By devotion and surrender to the Supreme (dhiyAvasuH), it illuminates=
 and invigorates (vaShTu) sacrifice of one's false notions about self (yaGY=
aM).
 
When the power of self-awareness is awakened and flows in the Sushum=
na nadi (Saraswati channel), various false notions of who we are (I am the =
body, this is mine etc) that are racing in our consciousness like horses ar=
e controlled and we are purified (i.e. ridden of false notions that make us=
 impure). As we are purified, our devotion and surrender to the Supreme (ak=
a True Self) increases and invigorates the sense of sacrifice in us (i.e. g=
iving up false notions of being and doership).
 
yaGYaM dadhe sarasvatI|| R=
V 1.3.11

1.3.11: The subtle energy channel that facilitates the flow of aw=
areness of True Self (sarasvatI) impels (codayitrI) the bliss of Truth (sUn=
R^itAnAM), awakens (cetantI) good thoughts based on Truth (sumatInAM) and s=
upports (dadhe) sacrifice of false notions about self (yaGYaM).
 
As the ho=
rses of false notions are controlled and one is purified (see 1.3.10), the =
next stage is described here. As the power of self-awareness flows further =
in the Sushumna nadi (Saraswati channel), one experiences the bliss of Trut=
h and good thoughts based in Truth. Thoughts based on false notions (e.g. I=
 am the body, this is mine) may bring happiness sometimes and sadness somet=
imes, but they can never bring the bliss of Truth. As self-awareness flows =
further in Sushumna nadi, one is established in good notions and bliss.
 
d=
hiyo vishvA virAjati||
 
1.3.12: The subtle energy channel that facilitates=
 the flow of awareness of True Self (sarasvatI) illumines and awakens one t=
o (pracetayati) the great ocean of Cosmic Self (maho arNaH) with absolute c=
larity (ketunA) and also throws light on and establishes (virAjati) multipl=
icity of consciousness (dhiyaH) and worlds (vishvAH).
 
This describes the =
next stage after what is described in 1.3.10 and 1.3.11. It describes what =
happens when the power of self-awareness rises the highest in Sushumna nadi=
. One is awakened to the great ocean of Cosmic Self, i.e. one realizes true=
 Self. Also, this Cosmic Self establishes itself as various limited intelle=
cts and objects and as various worlds that exist. One is aware of oneself a=
s the undivided cosmic self and also as various beings and worlds. One sees=
 various beings and worlds in oneself. Such an awareness of Self with absol=
ute clarity results with the power of self-awareness flows totally uninterr=
upted in the Sushumna/Saraswati channel.
 
